        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued October 25 at 10:13PM CDT by NWS Corpus Christi TX</headline>
        <description>At 1013 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Port Oconnor, moving northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Port Oconnor, Olivia, Schicke Point, Port Alto, Matagorda Island
State Park, and Indianola.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
